New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo had a triple-double with 11 points, 13 assists, and 12 rebounds, his fourth of the season.
The Milwaukee Bucks outscored the Toronto Raptors 63-24 in bench points.
Key Match Events: Antetokounmpo returned to finish his third career triple-double against the Raptors after a cut.
Bobby Portis' 20 points and a 20-2 run late in the first quarter turned the game in the Bucks' favor.
Pre-Game Insights: The Bucks were struggling with a 2-8 start but managed to handle the Raptors despite their recent struggles.
The Raptors were in a tough spot with 13 losses in 14 games.
Post-Match Reflections: The Raptors' young players showed promise but couldn't overcome the Bucks' performance.
The game marked the first time RJ Barrett, Scottie Barnes, and Immanuel Quickley played together.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks had a 33-point lead at one point.
Khris Middleton sat out due to an ankle injury.
Others: The Bucks and Raptors will play again on Wednesday, with Milwaukee hosting the San Antonio Spurs and Toronto starting a three-game trip.
